subject_prompt_600:
Liquor Control Board of Ontario Form
Fill out the Liquor Control Board of Ontario form if you are applying for a liquor licence in Ontario.

If you have any questions about your application, or need additional information, please contact the nearest LCBO store.
coupled_prompt_600:
Ontario allows breweries to sell their product in their own stores, although this is not currently available for all licensed producers. They are also allowed to sell online if they have a permit from the LCBO and it has been approved by the Ministry of Community Safety and Correctional Services (SCS). Beer stores sell both beer and wine and liquor stores sell both.  The LCBO distributes the majority of craft brewers' products. As of April 7, 2015 there were 8,831 craft breweries operating across Ontario with another 3,039 brewing facilities in development.     There is now a license for the production of wine at 886 sites, including 438 wineries and 1 winery brewery. These numbers represent only those that are active breweries and do not include the over 20,000 "microbreweries" which have grown in the past 10 years.
